  <Quality>The data has been produced for small scale use only.

Definitions of the territories as compiled by R.K.Headland (Scott Polar Research Institute) 20 April 1998 from historical information and presented at an Antarctic Treaty meeting. Bruce Hull (Policy AAD) provided a copy to the Australian Antarctic Data Centre.

The dataset consists of three shapefiles for use in a Geographical Information System (GIS).
1. Polygon data representing each claim. The data are stored with a polar stereographic projection.
2. Line data representing each claim. The data is stored with a polar stereographic projection.
3. Line data representing each claim. The data are stored unprojected in latitudes and longitudes.

Territorial claim boundary lines of longitude generated at 0.1 degree intervals. Boundaries clipped to the Antarctic coastline using 1:10 million scale data from the Antarctic Digital Database version 5.

The northern and southern limit of Norway's claim is undefined.</Quality>
  <Access_Constraints>Stored data format: ArcView shapefiles. Available format type: ArcView shapefiles. Stored in a polar stereographic projection

These data are publicly available for download from the provided URL.</Access_Constraints>
